The paper focuses on computer vision and object detection, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses advanced computing resources and analyzes large amounts of data, which suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. The use of video cameras and analysis of consecutive images suggests a focus on multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the need for contextual information in training vision solutions, which suggests a focus on information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category.
